    <naif_host_id>VO1</naif_host_id>
    <description>The Viking spacecraft consisted of two orbiters and their heat-sterilized landers, each weighing 3530 kg at launch and 900 kg and 600 kg post-landing for orbiters and landers, respectively. The orbiters, designed from earlier Mariner models, utilized solar panels for power and employed solar and star sensors for stabilization. Key instruments included high-resolution cameras, a near-infrared spectrometer, and an infrared thermal mapper. The landers were equipped with stereo cameras, meteorological instruments, chemical analysis tools, biology experiments, and a seismometer. The systems allowed for soil and atmospheric measurements, and the landers could also analyze samples using a programmable arm. The orbiterâ€™s instruments were mounted on a scan platform that allowed for controlled movement to facilitate observations.</description>
